  "doc_id": "22230",
  "text": "Myoblasts. Recent several studies have suggested that induction of ceramide is caused by various stressors [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . HPLC was used to quantify ceramide upon microgravity by 3D-clinosstat in C2C12 myoblasts. Microgravity was induced by 3D-clinostat for 24 hr with or without EVP (50 g/mL). Exposure to microgravity for 24 hr caused the 2.01-fold increase of endogenous ceramide levels. However, EVP (50 g/mL) decreased endogenous ceramide levels by 23.61% (Figure 4) .",
